[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(40, 41) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For I lift up my hand.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—This is the form in taking an oath. (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 10:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) The two verses may be connected thus: “For I lift up my hand to heaven, and say, As I live for ever, if I whet my lightning sword, and my hand take hold on judgment, I will render vengeance to mine enemies, and repay them that hate me.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 32:40-42",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 32:40-42",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I lift up my hand to heaven — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I solemnly swear I will do what here follows. It was the custom to stretch out the hand in swearing, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 14:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And say, I live for ever — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As surely as I live for ever, I will whet my sword, &c. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If I whet ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— If once I begin to prepare for war, and for the execution of my sentence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Mine hand take hold on judgment — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The instruments of judgments, the weapons of war. A metaphor from warriors that take their weapons into their hands when they intend to fight. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Glittering sword — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the lightning of my sword. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A similitude which shows God’s judgments to be swift, powerful, and terrible, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 21:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 9:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I will render vengeance to mine enemies — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "No power shall be able to stop or hinder my proceedings. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I will make mine arrows drunk with blood — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I will execute vengeance upon them to the full. A strong poetical figure, implying the abundance of blood that should be shed. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The blood — of the captives — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Whom my sword hath sorely wounded, though not utterly killed. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The beginning of revenges — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "When once I begin to revenge myself and people upon mine and their enemies, and will go on and make a full end.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "32:39-43 This conclusion of the song speaks, 1. Glory to God. No escape can be made from his power. 2. It speaks terror to his enemies. Terror indeed to those who hate him. The wrath of God is here revealed from heaven against them. 3. It speaks comfort to his own people. The song concludes with words of joy. Whatever judgments are brought upon sinners, it shall go well with the people of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
